rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The primary entity that represents the collection of all coaches in American football. Currently this collection includes professional, collegiate, and amateur coaches.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Football Head Coach

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an American football coach to information about coaching positions that he or she has held in the course of a career.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The primary entity that represents the collection of all coach position types. This includes entities such as 'head coach', 'Defensive coordinator' and 'Special teams coordinator'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Football Coach Position

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property linking a standard descriptor for a coaching position, e.g. 'head coach', to information about people who have held this position.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Coaches

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all American football conferences. There are currently two conferences in professional American football. Each conference has 16 teams and are futher divided into divisions.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Football Conference

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:american_football.conference to its mso:american_football.division.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Divisions

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The regulated organization under which the team competes (NFL).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: League

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Teams

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of American football divisions. Each of the professional conferences in American football are divided into four divisions of four teams each. The division winners are guaranteed one of the top 4 seeds in the conference playoffs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Football Division

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:american_football.division to its mso:american_football.conference.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Conference

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Teams

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A relationship type that collects the date and the time of the player's 40-yd dash statistic. This statistic is intended to evaluate the speed of a player for collegiate recruiting and NFL draft.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Forty-yard dash time

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The date this time was recorded.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The player's time in seconds.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Time

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of American football games. This collection includes all professional and non-professional American football games. Note that this type covers forms of football played in both the United States and Canada.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Football Game

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The team that is not hosting the match. This could mean that they are visiting the other teams location, or arbitrarily assigned when the game is at a neutral location.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Away Team

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The date upon which the football game occurred.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Player statistics from a single game relating to passing the football.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Passing

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Player statistics from a single game relating to receiving the football.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Receiving

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Player statistics from a single game relating to rushing.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rushing

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The team hosting the game. This is most often based on location, but sometimes will be arbitrarily assigned for games held at neutral sites.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Home Team

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A complete cycle of preseason, regular season, and postseason competition (yearly).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Season

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A relationship type that collects the passing statistics for a given player of American football in a given game. Passing in American football is a throw by one player in an attempt to transfer the ball to another player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Game Passing Statistics

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Number of times the player passed the ball.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Attempts

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Number of times a pass resulted in a reception.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Completions

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that specifies the American football game about which statistics are provided.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Game

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Passing plays in which the opponent intercepted the ball.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Interceptions

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Longest passing play.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Longest Completion

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Player recording the statistics.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Player

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The passer rating for the game (algorithmic measure of passing performance).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rating

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Number of times the player was sacked.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sacks

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Team recording the statistics.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Team

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that indicates whether or not a touchdown was made on the basis of the longest pass in the given football game.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Touchdown on Longest Pass

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Passing plays that resulted in a touchdown.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Touchdowns

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Yards covered on passing plays.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Yards

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Yards lost of plays in which the player was sacked.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Yards Lost on Sacks

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A relationship type that collects the receiving statistics for a given player of American football in a given game. Reception is part of a play in which a forward pass from behind the line of scrimmage is caught by a player in bounds.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Game Receiving Statistics

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that specifies the football game about which statistics are provided.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Game

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Length of longest reception by the player in the game
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Longest

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Player that recorded the stats.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Player

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Number of catches by the player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Receptions

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Team on which the stats were recorded.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Team

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: True if touchdown was scored on players longest reception.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Touchdown on Longest Reception

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Touchdowns scored on plays in which the player caught the ball.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Touchdowns

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Yards covered on passing plays caught by the player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Yards

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A relationship type that collects the rushing statistics for a given player of American football in a given game. Rushing in this sense is the action by an offensive player to advance the ball by running with it instead of passing the ball.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Game Rushing Statistics

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Number of times the player rushed the ball.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Carries

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that specifies the football game about which statistics are provided.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Game

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Length of longest carry by the player in the game.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Longest

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Player recording the stats.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Player

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Team on which the stats were recorded.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Team

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that indicates whether or not a touchdown was made on the basis of the longest rush in the given game.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Touchdown on Longest Carry

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Touchdowns scored on rushing plays.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Touchdowns

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Yards covered on rushing plays.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Yards

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A relationship type that collects the score for a given football game with the teams that played in the game.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Football game score

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the game for which a score is provided.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Game

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the score of the given game.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Score

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A relationship type that collects facts about a given coach of American football and his coaching position for a particular team, including the type of coaching position, team, and start and stop dates. This relationship type is intended to be the former coaching positions for a coach. See mso:american_football.coach.current_team_head_coached for the current team fact. (Note this is not an ideal representation and is slated for changes)
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Football Historical Coach Position

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the coach about which position information is provided.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Coach

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the date on which the coach first occupied the given position.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: From

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Role or title of the position (head coach, defensive coordinator, linebackers coach, etc...)
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Position

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the team that was coached in the given position.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Team

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the date on which the coach last occupied the given position.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: To

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A relationship type that collects facts about a given player of American football and his playing participation in a given team. Facts include the player's position, jersey number, and starting and ending dates on the team. See mso:american_football.roster_position for the collection of facts about the player's current team. (Note this is not an ideal representation and is slated for changes)
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Football Historical Roster Position

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Starting date for a player on a previous team.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: From

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Previous uniform number for a football player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Football player that played on a previous team.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Player

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Previous position played by a player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Position(s)

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Previous team for a player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Team

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The date the player left the team he previously played for.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: To

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of NFL games. These include all pre-season, regular season, and post-season NFL games.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: NFL Game

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The week number for the NFL football season. This includes regular season weeks 1 through 17, and the postseason. The postseason is marked as weeks 18, 19, 20, and 21, representing the Wild Card, Divisional Playoffs, Conference Championships, and Super Bowl, respectively. The preseason is not included.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Week

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all professional players of American football. Note that this type covers players of forms of football played in both the United States and Canada.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Football Player

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a player of American football to the number of career assisted tackles attributed to the player in professional games. Assisted tackles are not an officially tracked NFL statistic, and so teams have different standards for attributing assisted tackles.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Assisted Tackles

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a football player to an award that was received by the athlete.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Award

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to his career losses, the number of professional games the player's team lost.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Career Losses

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to his career ties, the number of professional games the player's team tied.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Career Ties

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to his career winning percentage.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Winning Pct

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to his career wins, the number of professional games the player's team won.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Career Wins

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The ilkid from databaseFootball.com
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: databaseFootball.com ID

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to the number of fair catches the player achieved in professional games. A fair catch is an attempt to catch a ball kicked by the opposing team without interference.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fair Catches

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a football player to the identifier for the player assigned by the Football Almanac.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Football Almanac Identifier

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a football player to the identifier for the player assigned by footballdb.com.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Footballdb Identifier

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a player of American football to the number of forced fumbles attributed to the player in professional games.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Forced Fumbles

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:american_football.player to the mso:american_football.historical_roster_position(s) the player has held on given teams.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Former Teams

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The time it takes this player to run 40 yards (typically measured during recruiting or drafts).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: 40-yard dash time

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to the total number of yards accumulated after a ball has been fumbled, then recovered in professional games.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fumble Yards

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a football player to statistical information about the player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Games

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to his career interception touchdowns.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Int. TD

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to his career interception yards.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Int. Yds

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to his career interceptions.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Player Interceptions

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to his career kicking extra points.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Extra Points

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to his career kicking extra points attempted.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Extra Points Att.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to his career kicking extra points percentage.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Extra Points Pct.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a player of American football to the number of career successful field goals.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Field Goals

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to his number of career attempted field goals.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Field Goals Att.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to his career field goal percentage.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Field Goals Pct.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to his career longest field goal.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Longest Goal

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to his career yards per kick.
Property relating a player of American football to the number of yards representing the longest punt for the player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Longest Punt

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to his career passes defended.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Passes Defended

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to the career passing attempts for the player in professional games. Passing attempts can result in a reception, incompletion or interception.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Passing Attempts

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to the career number of passing completions in professional games. Passing completions are those passes successfully executed by the player and caught by a receiver.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Passing Completions

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to the percentage of pass attempts that were successfully completed in professional games. This is calculated by dividing the number of completions by the number of passing attempts.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Passing Completion Percentage

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to the career number of interceptions on passes thrown by the player in professional games. An interception is when a pass is succesfully caught by an opposing player. See also mso:american_football.player.interceptions, which defines the interceptions a player has caught.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Passing Interceptions

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to the career passing yards per touchdown in professional games. This is the number of yards gained by the player in passing divided by the number of touchdowns attributed to the player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Passing Yrds Per TD

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Passing statistics for an individual player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Passing

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Receiving statistics for an individual player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Receiving

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Rushing statistics for an individual player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rushing

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a football player to a standard descriptor for a position on a football team held by the player, e.g. quarterback.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Position

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to the career number of punts returned in professional games. Punts returned are the punts caught or picked up by a player on the punt receiving team.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Punts Returned

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to the player's career number of punt return touchdowns in professional games. These are touchdowns that occur when the player receives a punt and then returns the kick the length of the field into the end zone.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Punt Return Touchdowns

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to the player's career number of yards punted in professional games. This is the total number of years that a punt travels before it is intercepted or enters the end zone.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Punt Yards

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to the number of punts inside the 20 yard line, the number of times the player punts inside the 20 yard line in professional games. Note that a touchback is not an inside-20.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Punts Inside 20

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to the longest punt in yards the player achieved during a professional game.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Longest Punt

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to the total yards punted the player was responsible for during professional games.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Total Yards Punted

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to the career number of touchback the player was responsible for in professional games.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Touchbacks

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to the average yards per punt, which is the total number of punted yards divided by the number of punts the player took during professional games.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Yards Per Punt

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating the player of American football to the number of sacks on the quarterback, the tackling of the quarterback of the opposite team behind the line of scrimmage, the player had in professional games.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Quarterback Sacks

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property that relates a player of American football to the number of career fumbles when receiving, the number of times the player fumbled in a professional game.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fumbles

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to the career total receiving touchdowns attributed to the player in professional games. These are touchdowns scored after a pass has been caught, and the receiver makes it into the end-zone.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Receiving Touch Downs

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to the career total yards the player acheived during returns in professional games. See also mso:american_football.player.returns.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Return Yards

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to the career number of returns acheived in professioanl games. Returns are attempts to advance the ball closer to the opposing team's goal line after ball possession has changed. Returns include kickoffs, punts, fumbles, and interceptions.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Returns

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to the career number of touchdowns the player acheived during returns in professional games. See also mso:american_football.player.returns
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Returns For Touchdowns

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to the career number of recovered fumbles in professional games.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fumbles Recovered

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to the career number of yards gained in recovered fumbles in professional games.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Recovered Fumbles Yards

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to the number of career touchdowns made while rushing in professional games. Rushing touchdowns occur when the ball is carried into the endzone rather than passed into the endzone.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rushing TDs

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to the career number of yards earned in rushing in professional games.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rushing Yards

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to the career average yards per rushing attempt.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Yards Per Attempt

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating the player of American football to the number of sacks, the tackling of an offensive player on the opposite team behind the line of scrimmage, the player had in professional games.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sacks

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a player of American football to the number of solo tackles attributed to the player in professional games. Solo tackles are not an officially tracked NFL statistic, and so teams my have different standards for attributing solo tackles.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Solo Tackles

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to the total number of career points attributed to the player in professional games.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Total Points

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to his career total number of receiving yards in professional games. Receiving yards are the yards gained by the player after a pass completion.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Total Receiving Yds

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to the career total rushing yards attributed to the player in professional games. Rushing yards are those yards gained in rushing, running the ball when starting behind the line of scrimmage.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Total Rushing Yds

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a player of American football to the total number of carrer tackles attributed to player in professional games. Total tackles are calculated by adding solo and assisted tackles. Neither solo nor assisted tackles are official NFL statistics, so teams may have differing standards for attributing tackles.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Total Tackles

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to the number of career touchdowns attributed to the player in professional games.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Total TDs

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to the career total offensive yards the player gained in professional games.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Total Yds

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a player of American football to the career total yards earned per professional game played. This is calculated by dividing the number of rushing yards by the number of games played.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The relationship collecting data on an mso:american_football.player's defensive season statistics. These are the general stats that are available for all defensive line players: linebacker, defensive tackle, cornerback, safety, and defensive end. For statistics for the player's specific positions, see the relationships mso:american_football.player_rushing_statistics, mso:american_football.player_receiving_statistics, and so forth.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Season Defensive Statistics

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:american_football.season_defensive_statistics to the number of assisted tackles attributed to an mso:american_football.player in professional games for a given mso:sports.season. Assisted tackles are not an officially tracked NFL statistic, and so teams may have different standards for attributing assisted tackles.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Assisted Tackles

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:american_football.season_statistics to the number of forced fumbles attributed to an mso:american_football.player in professional games for a given mso:sports.season. Forced fumbles are those fumbles the defender forced the opponent to lose control of the ball before a tackle or score.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Forced Fumbles

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:american_football.season_statistics to the number of touchdowns scored after making an interception attributed to an mso:american_football.player in professional games for a given mso:sports.season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Interception Touchdowns

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:american_football.season_statistics to the number of interceptions yards attributed to an mso:american_football.player in professional games for a given mso:sports.season. Interception yards are the total number of yards gained by a defender after making an interception.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Inception Yards

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:american_football.season_statistics to the number of interceptions attributed to an mso:american_football.player in professional games for a given mso:sports.season. Interceptions are those times a defender successfully catches a pass from an opposing passer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Interceptions

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:american_football.season_statistics to the number of passes defended by an mso:american_football.player in professional games for a given mso:sports.season. These are the incomplete passes caused by the player by slapping or blocking the ball.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Pass Defended

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:american_football.season_defensive_statistics to the mso:american_football.player for whom the statistics hold true for the given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Player

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:american_football.season_defensive_statistics to the number of sacks attributed to an mso:american_football.player in professional games for a given mso:sports.season. A sack occurs when the quarterback (or a player acting as a passer) is tackled behind the line of scrimmage before he can throw a forward pass, when the quarterback is tackled behind the line of scrimmage in the "pocket" and his intent is unclear, or when a passer runs out of bounds behind the line of scrimmage due to defensive pressure.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sacks

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:american_football.season_defensive_statistics to the number of yards lost as a result of the mso:american_football.player's sacks for a given mso:sports.season.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:american_football.season_statistics to the mso:sports.season to which the statistic applies.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Season

Solo tackles are not an officially tracked NFL statistic, and so teams may have different standards for attributing solo tackles.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Solo Tackles

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:american_football.season_statistics to the number of total tackles for a given mso:american_football.player during a given mso:sports.season. Total tackles are the accumulation of assisted tackles and solo tackles.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tackles
